TY  - JOUR
AU  - Subrahmanyam, Avanidhar
AU  - Titman, Sheridan
T1  - Financial Market Shocks and the Macroeconomy
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hht058
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 26
IS  - 11
SP  - 2687
EP  - 2717
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - Feedback from stock prices to cash flows occurs because information revealed by firms' stock prices influences the actions of competitors. We explore the implications of feedback within a noisy rational expectations setting with incumbent publicly traded firms and privately held new entrants. In this setting the equilibrium relation among stock prices and both future dividends and aggregate output depends on the strategic environment in which these firms operate. In general, under reasonable conditions, the relations between prices, dividends, and economic output in our framework are consistent with empirical evidence in the macroliterature. We also generate new, potentially testable, implications.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hht058
ER  - 



