TY  - JOUR
AU  - Choi, Jaewon
T1  - What Drives the Value Premium?: The Role of Asset Risk and Leverage
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hht040
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 26
IS  - 11
SP  - 2845
EP  - 2875
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper shows empirically how asset risk and financial leverage interact to explain the equity risk dynamics of value versus growth stocks. During economic downturns, the asset betas and leverage of value firms increase, contributing to a sharp rise in equity betas. Asset betas of growth firms are much less sensitive to economic conditions, and, consistent with the tradeoff theory of capital structure, growth firms are also less levered, contributing to the relative stability of their equity betas. By incorporating instruments that better capture beta dynamics, I show that the interactions of conditional betas with the market risk premium and volatility explain approximately 40% of the unconditional value premium.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hht040
ER  - 



